---
import ProjectLayout from "../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro";
---

<ProjectLayout title="VibeTrip - AI Travel Planning Platform">
  <h1 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">VibeTrip</h1>

  <div class="mb-4">
    <a
      href="https://vibetrip.app"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
      class="inline-flex items-center space-x-2 text-primary-400 hover:text-primary-300 font-mono font-semibold"
    >
      <svg
        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
        width="24"
        height="24"
        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        fill="none"
        stroke="currentColor"
        stroke-width="2"
        stroke-linecap="round"
        stroke-linejoin="round"
        class="w-5 h-5"
      >
        <path d="M5 12h14"></path>
        <path d="m12 5 7 7-7 7"></path>
      </svg>
      <span>→ vibetrip.app</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100 mt-2">Overview</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    VibeTrip is an AI travel planner that turns a short onboarding wizard — group, dates,
    destination, budget, goals, interests — into three complete, day-by-day itineraries with
    accommodations, activities, and timed slots, for a single credit. Research is powered by
    Gemini with live Google Search grounding, so plans reflect current information rather than
    generic travel lists.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Key Features</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Resumable Trip Wizard</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    A seven-step onboarding flow that can be left and resumed at any point, capturing traveler
    profiles and preferences before any credit is spent.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Three Itineraries per Generation</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Each generation produces three distinct, complete plans — accommodations, 8+ activities and
    places each, with timed daily slots — so travelers compare real options instead of editing a
    single guess.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Grounded AI Research</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Gemini Flash with Google Search grounding researches destinations live, layered on a
    pre-seeded knowledge base of ~50 destinations that eliminates cold starts for popular places.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Real-Time Generation Progress</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Convex realtime subscriptions stream generation progress to the UI, keeping a long-running
    AI pipeline transparent instead of leaving users on a spinner.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Technology Stack</h2>

  <ul class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Frontend</strong>: React 19, TanStack Router (SPA), Tailwind CSS; Astro 5 marketing site</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Backend</strong>: Convex (realtime database and functions)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">AI</strong>: Gemini Flash via the AI SDK, with Google Search grounding</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Payments</strong>: Stripe one-time credit packs with auto-refund on failure</li>
    <li><strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Infra</strong>: Vercel, Resend, PostHog, Sentry</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Key Challenges</h2>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Reliability of Long-Running Generations</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    A generation state machine with guardrails, cron-based stale-job recovery, and idempotent
    auto-refunds ensures users never lose a credit to a failed or stuck pipeline.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Schema-Driven AI Output</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    Itineraries are compiled against strict schemas so the model's research reliably becomes
    structured plans — accommodations, activities, and timed slots — rather than free-form text.
  </p>

  <h3 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Full-Product Rebuild</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    VibeTrip started as a Next.js + FastAPI + CrewAI multi-agent system on AWS. It was rebuilt
    from scratch on Convex and grounded Gemini — trading agent orchestration complexity for a
    simpler, faster, more reliable production architecture.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Project Impact</h2>

  <p class="text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
    VibeTrip showcases end-to-end product engineering: payments with real money-back guarantees,
    grounded AI research, realtime UX, and the judgment to rebuild on a simpler architecture when
    the first one fought back.
  </p>
</ProjectLayout>
